      Derivative markets
   =20
 =20
Let=E2=80=99s say that you like the stock of AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc=
. and you want to buy, say, $1,000 worth of it. Let=E2=80=99s say you don=
=E2=80=99t have $1,000. How can you buy the stock anyway? A classic answer =
is =E2=80=9Ca margin loan=E2=80=9D: You go to your broker, put in $500, you=
r broker lends you $500, and you buy $1,000 worth of stock. When you sell i=
t, you have to pay your broker back, and you have to pay interest, but if i=
t goes up you get basically all of the upside.What if you don=E2=80=99t hav=
e $500? You might look into options. A call option to buy 100 shares of AMC=
 stock (about $3,600 worth) for $60 a share next month currently goes for a=
bout $200.[10] If you buy that and AMC doubles to $72 next month, you will =
make $1,000.[11] That=E2=80=99s roughly what you would have made buying $1,=
000 worth of stock. Of course if it goes up less you=E2=80=99ll make less; =
if it goes up 50% you=E2=80=99ll make nothing and lose your $200. This is n=
ot a perfect substitute for buying the stock. But it=E2=80=99s something. I=
t=E2=80=99s a leveraged bet on the stock, a way to spend a relatively small=
 amount of money to bet on a huge rally in AMC stock.What if you don=E2=80=
=99t have $200? What if you have, say, zero dollars? Will anyone provide yo=
u with leverage where you put up nothing, they put up the money, you buy th=
e AMC stock, if it goes up you collect the profits, and you never pay them =
back? When you put it like that the answer is no, obviously not, but it=E2=
=80=99s worth a try?Here is  an article from Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Michael Re=
gan=C2=A0about GoFundMe as a platform for financing AMC investments:=E2=80=
=9CHello fellow Apes!=E2=80=9D reads one pitch from a trader who=E2=80=99s =
so far only been able to buy a partial share. =E2=80=9CI am here asking for=
 help of any amount to buy AMC stonk! I work at my sad minimum wage job aka=
 McDonald=E2=80=99s and barely have one share of AMC. Money is tight, I sur=
vive off $1 menu and eat ramen. Hopefully I will have 1 share soon!=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=A6Many simply implore potential donors to contribute to traders =
who want to buy and hold more AMC shares so they can worsen a short-squeeze=
 among hedge funds betting against the stock. Details are scant on why exac=
tly that would be a better strategy than the donors simply buying the share=
s themselves.No, I=E2=80=99m kidding. While the GoFundMe pitches for, uh =
=E2=80=A6=C2=A0margin donations? =E2=80=A6=C2=A0are the most=C2=A0financial=
ly=C2=A0interesting ones =E2=80=94=C2=A0imagine starting a hedge fund funde=
d by donations! =E2=80=94=C2=A0most of the pitches are actually to fund air=
plane banners:Airborne messages pumping shares of AMC Entertainment Holding=
s Inc. -- similar to the banner planes that alert parched Jersey Shore tour=
ists to where they can find a $2 Corona Light -- have become a top tool of =
choice for the retail army that is marching in formation for this cult stoc=
k. Pilots don=E2=80=99t come cheap, so the self-described =E2=80=9Capes=E2=
=80=9D of the AMC message boards are looking for handouts to help the effor=
t: $4,250 for a flight over Canada; $550 to hoist =E2=80=9CAMC TO THE MOON =
HODL=E2=80=9D above North Carolina; $3,000 to fly a similar message above W=
all Street; 5,000 pounds so that the British Parliament gets the word. And =
so on.One thing that I have said about the meme-stock craze is that retail =
traders on Reddit have rapidly developed a very sophisticated collective un=
derstanding of=C2=A0how to move stock prices. There is a lot of crowdsource=
d knowledge about how to get the most bang for your buck, how to leverage a=
 relatively small investment of your own money  into large purchases by opt=
ions market makers and squeezed short sellers to push the stock up. (Some o=
f the meme-stock issuers, particularly AMC, have also learned to play this =
game, to  do publicity stunts that move their stock prices up and allow the=
m to raise cash.) From where I sit, spending a few thousand dollars to fly =
banners saying =E2=80=9CAMC TO THE MOON HODL=E2=80=9D=C2=A0over random beac=
hes does=C2=A0not=C2=A0seem like a particularly cost-effective way to boost=
 your portfolio; I would not expect that to drive the stock price up very m=
uch. But I am willing to believe that the AMC apes might have a better hand=
le on this stuff than I do.Also though the point of investing in meme stock=
s is not=C2=A0just=C2=A0to make money, it is also to have fun and feel like=
 part of a cultural phenomenon. I suppose the banners help with that.=C2=A0=
Also here=E2=80=99s this:Brian Merli made a comment stating - "when amc hot=
 $30 I'll eat a dog turd"=C2=A0Since then Brian has not came through with h=
is promise. Apes you know what to do! Let's spread Brian's photo and quote =
on billboards all over St. Louis, Missouri! 5k is the target price but we a=
re apes! Let's spread Brian's face across the country! Buy more AMC!I don=
=E2=80=99t see how that would help the stock price. It has raised $315. I d=
unno.
